The issue with Porsche patent ring synchros is not brass. It't the 
molybdenum surface of the synchros that wear out too fast because the GL-5 
is too slick. That surface is designed to grab the brass dog teeth and if 
it slips too much, it wears off the moly grit and gear clash results.
